Wordsmyth Vocabulary Inventory (WVI)&lt;br/&gt;
Headwords labeled with a number from 1 to 5 belong to the Wordsmyth Vocabulary Index (WVI), a list of 10,000 important vocabulary words grouped into five levels of difficulty, with level 1 words being the least difficult and level 5 the most difficult.&lt;br/&gt;
The five levels correspond approximately to five grade-level bands:&lt;br/&gt;

level 1 grades K-2&lt;br/&gt;
level 2 grades 3-6&lt;br/&gt;
level 3 grades 7-9&lt;br/&gt;
level 4 grades 10-12&lt;br/&gt;
level 5 grades 12+&lt;br/&gt;

The core of the WVI words were selected by analyzing the Educator&apos;s Word Frequency Guide (WFG), which provides grade-specific data on word frequency for words taken from a 17-million-word corpus of texts used in K-12+ education.&lt;br/&gt;
Words used across the curriculum were given precedence over domain-specific vocabulary. This general academic vocabulary corresponds with the &quot;Tier 2 words&quot; newly emphasized in the Common Core State Standards for literacy.&lt;br/&gt;
Additional established vocabulary word resources, such as Coxhead&apos;s Academic Word List (AWL), Elfriede Hiebert&apos;s Word Zones, and the Corpus of Contemporary American English 6000 most frequent words, were consulted to both narrow down and validate our initial reservoir of vocabulary words.&lt;br/&gt;

Data from https://www.wordsmyth.net/;&lt;br/&gt;
